{
  "stem": "13690.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "At that date, they locked them in and they said, if the town will not behave, or there will be any discomfort for the Germans or any uprising or any shootings or anything which-- extraordinary, the four will be killed.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was quiet.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I don't know because of the four people, just people did not resist.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My father was released.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They kept them for 48 hours.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Going back to the ghetto, which people could not go out, obviously, a lot of people starting to go out without permission, without any means of papers.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "If they were caught, there were killed.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And there was a lot of their killings.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I would say most of the guards were Germans with also some black police-- which, there were black uniforms, but there were Poles.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I did not-- I was too young to work.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And my father did not have to go to work.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They were taking people to various stations to work.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The stations, mainly, what they did was just to keep the highway clean.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The highway that ran through our city was one of the most important crossing points into the heart of Poland, and at the same time going west into the heart of Germany.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So that highway-- so to say, in those days, a highway-- it was not a six-lane highway like in Los Angeles or California-- but it was a highway, well-kept road, which they always tried to keep it clean, especially in the wintertime.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "When snow fell, that road had to be constantly cleaned.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So, actually, what is the date of the start of the ghetto?",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "When did they actually start the ghetto?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I would say the ghetto-- towards the end-- 1940, 1941-- and was going on until 1942 during the high holiday period.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That's correct.",
      "word_count": 2
    }
  ],
